ment=jawiki redirects to 古代日本の戸籍制度}}, compiled in 690 AD under the [[:en:Asuka Kiyomihara Code|Asuka Kiyomihara Code]], represented the next stage in census development. It detailed all households and individuals, enabling the implementation of the {{ill|Handen-Shūju System|ja|班田収授法|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Handen-Shūju System|qq=}} and comprehensive tax collection. == Census Records and Reused Documents == Due to the high value of paper in ancient Japan, discarded census records were often reused by temples and government offices for other purposes. Many such reused documents, now known as {{ill|Recycled Paper Documents|ja|紙背文書|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Recycled Paper Documents|qq=}}, have been preserved in collections such as the [[:en:Shōsōin|Shōsōin]]. == Conclusion == The comprehensive compilation of census records continued until the mid-10th century but declined as the [[:en:Ritsuryō|Ritsuryō system]] weakened. The establishment of the {{ill|Shōen system|ja|荘園制|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōen system|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 荘園}} reduced the need for centralized population management, marking the end of systematic census compilation. == Related Chronology == - 540 AD: Census registration of immigrant groups. - 670 AD: Compilation of the Kōgo Census. - 690 AD: Compilation of the Kōin Census under the Asuka Kiyomihara Code. - 702 AD: The oldest surviving census, the {{ill|Hanpurī Census|ja|半布里戸籍|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hanpurī Census|qq=}}, was compiled. == References == <references/> == Further Reading == * {{Cite journal|author=Atsushi Nito |title=Research on Shōsōin Documents |journal=National Museum of Japanese History Bulletin |date=2014-12 |volume=192 |pages=57–64 |url=https://doi.org/10.15024/00002189|qq=}} == See Also == * [[:en:Ritsuryō|Ritsuryō system]] * {{ill|Handen-Shūju System|ja|班田収授法|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Handen-Shūju System|qq=}} * {{ill|Ancient Japanese Provincial Administration|ja|古代日本の地方官制|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ancient Japanese Provincial Administration|qq=}} * {{ill|Census Records|ja|計帳|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Census Records|qq=}}
